[+++ b/docs/reference/index-modules/codec.asciidoc, +[[codec-bloom-load]], +[TIP], +==================================================, +, +It can sometime make sense to disable bloom filters. For instance, if you are, +logging into an index per day, and you have thousands of indices, the bloom, +filters can take up a sizable amount of memory. For most queries you are only, +interested in recent indices, so you don't mind queries on older indices, +taking slightly longer., +, +In these cases you can disable loading of the bloom filter on  a per-index, +basis by updating the index settings:, +, +[source,js], +--------------------------------------------------, +PUT /old_index/_settings?index.codec.bloom.load=false, +--------------------------------------------------, +, +This setting, which defaults to `true`, can be updated on a live index. Note,, +however, that changing the value will cause the index to be reopened, which, +will invalidate any existing caches., +, +==================================================, +, +++ b/docs/reference/index-modules/codec.asciidoc, +[[codec-bloom-load]], +[TIP], +==================================================, +, +It can sometime make sense to disable bloom filters. For instance, if you are, +logging into an index per day, and you have thousands of indices, the bloom, +filters can take up a sizable amount of memory. For most queries you are only, +interested in recent indices, so you don't mind queries on older indices, +taking slightly longer., +, +In these cases you can disable loading of the bloom filter on  a per-index, +basis by updating the index settings:, +, +[source,js], +--------------------------------------------------, +PUT /old_index/_settings?index.codec.bloom.load=false, +--------------------------------------------------, +, +This setting, which defaults to `true`, can be updated on a live index. Note,, +however, that changing the value will cause the index to be reopened, which, +will invalidate any existi